comments: Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Jones' (NOP) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Graham (NOP) is already in O'Neale's (UTA) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Gobert (UTA) briefly grasps Ingram's (NOP) jersey at the end of his drive and he is able to move through the marginal contact.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Valanciunas (NOP) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to UTA.
Jones Jr. (NOP) and Mitchell (UTA) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Graham (NOP) places his forearm to Conley's (UTA) back after his gather and marginal contact occurs.
Valanciunas (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Conley's (UTA) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Bogdanovic (UTA) makes marginal contact with Jones (NOP) and releases as they pursue the loose ball.
Valanciunas (NOP) and Gobert (UTA) engage and disengage with one another for the loose ball.
Jones (NOP) briefly places his arm to Mitchell's (UTA) side and removes it as he cleanly dislodges the driving shot attempt before incidental contact occurs.
Graham (NOP) and Conely (UTA) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Jones (NOP) wraps Gobert (UTA) during the handoff and the contact affects his FOM.
Hart (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in O'Neale's (UTA) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Gobert (UTA) makes contact to Ingram's (NOP) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Jones (NOP) makes contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Mitchell (UTA) makes marginal contact to Valanciunas' (NOP) arm as the ball becomes dislodged. Mitchell then makes incidental foot to foot with Valaniciunas  as they pursue the loose ball.
Conley (UTA) legally contests Graham's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
O'Neale (UTA) briefly grasps Ingram's (UTA) arm off ball and immediately disengages.
Valanciunas (NOP) makes marginal contact with Conley (UTA) off ball that does not affect his ability to defend the pass.
Temple (NOP) briefly places his hand to Gobert's (UTA) side and immediately slides his hand off as they disengage.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in Hart's (NOP) path and makes incidental foot to foot contact as they disengage.

Replay review of the foul called on Gobert (UTA) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Gobert (UTA) delivers contact to Temple (NOP) during the screen and the contact affects his ability to defend.
